student loan problem.

04:05.100 --> 04:10.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Where do you see the major
differences and the major
flash points now with
the new administration?

04:10.033 --> 04:15.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANYA KAMENETZ: Well, I think we
saw, with Obama taking office
right around the financial

04:17.133 --> 04:20.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
crisis, the creation of
the Consumer Financial
Protection Bureau, which
became a major watchdog

04:20.066 --> 04:25.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on behalf of students, and many,
many actions taken against the
for-profit sector, but really

04:26.266 --> 04:28.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
also against student
lenders in general.

04:28.500 --> 04:33.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's been a real atmosphere
of, I would say, crackdown
in regulation and consumer

04:34.100 --> 04:36.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
advocacy.

04:36.566 --> 04:40.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the tenor has
certainly changed in
terms of the announcements
coming out of the DeVos

04:40.066 --> 04:42.166 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
administration.

04:42.166 --> 04:45.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She has hired former for-profit
college students - - sorry --
she has hired former for-profit

04:45.700 --> 04:50.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
college executives to advise
her, as well as putting in
charge of federal student aid

04:51.866 --> 04:53.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the CEO of a private
student loan company.

04:53.966 --> 04:58.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
